Design a Firebase product data architecture that serves both:

1. the application frontend and protocol engine
2. a future synchronization with Zoho Books Items and Price Lists

We are starting with products only.

Do not model Firebase as a copy of Zoho Books.
Instead, create a product-centered architecture with a clean separation between:

- product identity
- app-facing content
- inventory / operational fields
- Zoho integration metadata
- pricing layer

==================================================
PRIMARY OBJECTIVE
==================================================

Create a scalable Firebase product structure that:

- works well for the app today
- supports future Zoho Books synchronization
- avoids fragile text-based relationships
- keeps pricing flexible
- is easy to query in Firestore

==================================================
ANALYZE THE PROVIDED CSV STRUCTURES
==================================================

Use the uploaded CSV files as reference inputs:

1. Item.csv
2. Price_lists.csv

Extract the important concepts from those files and use them to inform the Firebase design.

The solution must take into account that:

- Items include SKU, descriptions, product type, inventory flags, tax fields, purchase/sales fields, status, usage unit, vendor, and custom fields
- Price Lists include both fixed_percentage and per_item logic
- Some price lists use unit pricing
- Some price lists use volume pricing
- A product may belong to multiple price lists

==================================================
FIREBASE DATA MODEL TO DESIGN
==================================================

Create the following core collections:

1. products
2. categories
3. subcategories
4. price_lists

Optional if useful:
5. vendors
6. locations

==================================================
PRODUCT DOCUMENT REQUIREMENTS
==================================================

Each product document must support:

A. Stable identity
- internal product id
- slug
- canonical name
- aliases
- status
- visibility

B. App-facing content
- display name
- short description
- long description
- category id
- subcategory id
- brand
- tags
- presentation (strength, form, pack size)
- media
- linked FAQ ids
- linked protocol ids

C. Inventory / operational fields
- sellable
- purchasable
- track_inventory
- stock_on_hand
- reorder_point
- location ids
- unit of measure

D. Zoho integration metadata
- zoho item_id
- zoho sku
- zoho status
- tax name
- tax percentage
- tax type
- reference_id
- last_sync_time
- account codes if needed

E. Pricing references
- base rate snapshot if useful
- currency code
- price_list_ids

==================================================
PRICE LIST DOCUMENT REQUIREMENTS
==================================================

Design price_lists to support:

1. fixed_percentage lists
2. per_item lists
3. volume pricing

Each price list document must support:

- internal id
- zoho price list id
- name
- currency code
- type
- status
- is default
- percentage if applicable
- is increase flag
- rounding type
- decimal place
- rules array

Each rule must support:

- product_id
- sku
- pricing_scheme
- start_quantity
- end_quantity
- rate
- discount if present

==================================================
RELATIONSHIP RULES
==================================================

Do not use product names as primary relational keys.

Use:

- internal product ids
- zoho item ids
- sku where useful

Relationships must be based on IDs, not display strings.

==================================================
OUTPUT REQUIRED
==================================================

Provide:

1. recommended Firebase schema
2. example document for products
3. example document for price_lists
4. example category and subcategory documents
5. field-level mapping from Firebase to Zoho Item.csv
6. field-level mapping from Firebase to Zoho Price_lists.csv
7. recommendations on which fields should live in Firebase and which should remain Zoho-only
8. recommendations for future sync workflow

==================================================
DESIGN PRINCIPLES
==================================================

The structure must be:

- normalized enough for clean sync
- simple enough for Firestore reads
- scalable
- app-friendly
- future-proof for Zoho Books integration

==================================================
FINAL OBJECTIVE
==================================================

Create a product architecture in Firebase that is optimized for the app today and properly prepared for a future integration with Zoho Books Items and Price Lists.